=Love is Always Online=

32
00:01:31,020 --> 00:01:33,940
=Episode 25=

33
00:01:34,740 --> 00:01:36,380
Wenqian,

34
00:01:36,380 --> 00:01:37,300
well,

35
00:01:37,300 --> 00:01:39,300
how could you do such a thing?

36
00:01:39,860 --> 00:01:41,620
What are you talking about?

37
00:01:41,620 --> 00:01:43,220
I'm his aunt and I care about him.

38
00:01:43,220 --> 00:01:44,340
Is that wrong?

39
00:01:45,420 --> 00:01:46,300
Caring is one thing,

40
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:47,220
but

41
00:01:47,220 --> 00:01:48,900
you can't use money to force them apart.

42
00:01:49,380 --> 00:01:51,500
Her uncle is just after money.

43
00:01:51,940 --> 00:01:53,820
Besides, he's Yao Yuan's family.

44
00:01:54,340 --> 00:01:55,740
He could've reasoned with her.

45
00:01:57,140 --> 00:01:58,540
If Anlan finds out about this,

46
00:01:59,260 --> 00:02:00,300
he will be furious.

47
00:02:00,860 --> 00:02:02,580
I was doing this to help him.

48
00:02:06,290 --> 00:02:07,980
Dad.

49
00:02:10,660 --> 00:02:12,140
How could you do this?

50
00:02:13,420 --> 00:02:14,500
I'm just doing this

51
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:15,940
for Anlan's happiness.

52
00:02:16,620 --> 00:02:18,900
Even if the Jiang family doesn't accept her,

53
00:02:19,620 --> 00:02:21,780
you can't settle it with money.

54
00:02:22,180 --> 00:02:23,380
That's so disrespectful.

55
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:26,020
You're trampling on their dignity.

56
00:02:26,020 --> 00:02:27,620
Dad, you don't know

57
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:29,620
how realistic girls are these days.

58
00:02:29,620 --> 00:02:31,420
Anlan has never dated before.

59
00:02:31,420 --> 00:02:32,700
I was afraid he'd be scammed,

60
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:34,500
so I tested her.

61
00:02:35,180 --> 00:02:36,620
And what did you get?

62
00:02:38,940 --> 00:02:40,900
Her uncle didn't take the money,

63
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:42,740
but maybe he just wants a higher price.

64
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:44,340
You are being irrational.

65
00:02:44,340 --> 00:02:45,300
I…

66
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:47,100
You are disgracing the Jiang family.

67
00:02:49,220 --> 00:02:50,060
Dad,

68
00:02:50,340 --> 00:02:51,380
I know I was wrong.

69
00:02:52,020 --> 00:02:53,820
Grandpa, please don't be angry.

70
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:55,780
That's right, Dad.

71
00:02:56,020 --> 00:02:57,300
Your health is what matters most.

72
00:02:57,660 --> 00:02:58,540
I'll take care

73
00:02:58,540 --> 00:03:00,020
of this matter.

74
00:03:01,340 --> 00:03:02,180
Fine.

75
00:03:03,020 --> 00:03:04,380
Don't make it look like

76
00:03:04,980 --> 00:03:05,940
the Jiang family

77
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:07,740
pushes people around.

78
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:09,740
Understood.

79
00:03:17,940 --> 00:03:20,140
Why didn't you back me up just now?

80
00:03:22,020 --> 00:03:23,220
Dad was so angry.

81
00:03:23,900 --> 00:03:25,060
What was I supposed to say?

82
00:03:25,060 --> 00:03:26,380
Nothing I said would have helped.

83
00:03:26,780 --> 00:03:28,580
So you just watched me become the target?

84
00:03:28,580 --> 00:03:29,420
Is that it?

85
00:03:29,740 --> 00:03:30,580
Wenqian,

86
00:03:31,140 --> 00:03:33,460
you were in the wrong this time.

87
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:35,420
Whatever.

88
00:03:35,420 --> 00:03:36,900
I won't meddle anymore.

89
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:37,740
Ridiculous.

90
00:03:46,220 --> 00:03:47,140
Your aunt

91
00:03:47,620 --> 00:03:49,620
was indeed too impulsive about this.

92
00:03:51,820 --> 00:03:52,660
Ancheng,

93
00:03:53,540 --> 00:03:54,860
please look out

94
00:03:55,260 --> 00:03:56,860
for Anlan more these days,

95
00:03:56,860 --> 00:03:57,700
okay?

96
00:03:58,460 --> 00:03:59,300
Mm.

97
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:05,050
I can't believe your aunt did that.

98
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:06,700
It's so outdated.

99
00:04:07,140 --> 00:04:08,740
Everyone has different values.

100
00:04:09,420 --> 00:04:10,260
What's your plan?

101
00:04:13,820 --> 00:04:15,380
I don't care if they agree or not.

102
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:18,070
My life is not for others to decide.

103
00:04:19,140 --> 00:04:20,670
I will not leave Yao Yuan.

104
00:04:22,500 --> 00:04:23,900
That's the spirit. I'm with you.

105
00:04:24,820 --> 00:04:26,700
Buddy, I've got a simple idea for you,

106
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:27,540
but it's effective.

107
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:29,180
You're not suggesting

108
00:04:29,180 --> 00:04:30,900
to make a done deal, are you?

109
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:31,820
You catch on quick.

110
00:04:32,660 --> 00:04:33,900
Whether it's in TV dramas

111
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:35,260
or real life,

112
00:04:35,260 --> 00:04:36,620
this move works every time.

113
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:39,620
I won't give up.

114
00:04:39,620 --> 00:04:40,620
I have to make those

115
00:04:40,620 --> 00:04:42,260
who oppose us see that

116
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:43,140
my wife

117
00:04:43,620 --> 00:04:44,900
can only be Yao Yuan.

118
00:04:46,020 --> 00:04:47,620
True. If you get married,

119
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:48,540
your family

120
00:04:48,540 --> 00:04:49,400
can't use such tactics

121
00:04:49,410 --> 00:04:50,820
to separate you.

122
00:04:51,860 --> 00:04:52,700
I support you.

123
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:55,220
Since you're getting married,

124
00:04:55,250 --> 00:04:55,970
do you want me

125
00:04:55,980 --> 00:04:57,220
to plan a surprise proposal?

126
00:04:58,220 --> 00:04:59,180
I suggest

127
00:04:59,180 --> 00:05:01,140
renting the tallest building in the city

128
00:05:01,140 --> 00:05:02,740
and setting off fireworks at night.

129
00:05:03,740 --> 00:05:04,580
Romantic, right?

130
00:05:04,580 --> 00:05:05,460
Too cliché.

131
00:05:05,860 --> 00:05:07,460
How about an island vacation?

132
00:05:07,460 --> 00:05:09,590
We could have a small party on the beach.

133
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:11,060
Singing and dancing all night.

134
00:05:11,060 --> 00:05:13,220
With the right music, venue,

135
00:05:13,220 --> 00:05:14,500
and vibe,

136
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:15,700
she would be moved.

137
00:05:16,060 --> 00:05:17,620
That's also cliché.

138
00:05:17,620 --> 00:05:19,860
TV shows have overused that.

139
00:05:20,060 --> 00:05:21,660
There's no surprise in that.

140
00:05:22,100 --> 00:05:23,520
How about Disneyland?

141
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:25,980
Dress up as Buzz Lightyear,

142
00:05:25,980 --> 00:05:27,540
walk towards her

143
00:05:27,540 --> 00:05:28,620
in the parade.

144
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:29,940
Then break out into a dance,

145
00:05:29,940 --> 00:05:31,540
and kneel to propose.

146
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:32,580
Now that is a surprise.

147
00:05:33,140 --> 00:05:36,220
The Boss dancing in a mascot suit to propose?

148
00:05:36,660 --> 00:05:38,020
Impossible.

149
00:05:38,020 --> 00:05:39,940
That's exactly why it's a surprise.

150
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:41,660
What do you say, Anlan?

151
00:05:41,660 --> 00:05:42,700
Whose idea is better?

152
00:05:44,020 --> 00:05:44,860
All terrible.

153
00:05:47,740 --> 00:05:48,700
Forget it.

154
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:49,860
We won't find an answer

155
00:05:49,860 --> 00:05:50,700
this way.

156
00:05:52,660 --> 00:05:54,140
What are you guys talking about?

157
00:05:56,780 --> 00:05:57,860
I ordered your orange juice.

158
00:05:59,460 --> 00:06:00,340
What's going on?

159
00:06:00,340 --> 00:06:01,300
What's so urgent?

160
00:06:01,630 --> 00:06:02,680
I wanted to see you,

161
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:04,300
and there's a big reason too.

162
00:06:05,020 --> 00:06:06,700
Someone needs your advice.

163
00:06:12,380 --> 00:06:13,740
I want to propose to Yao Yuan.

164
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:15,700
Propose?

165
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:17,380
Oh my god, that's amazing.

166
00:06:17,380 --> 00:06:19,660
Yuan will definitely be so happy.

167
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:22,540
Do you think she will say yes?

168
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:25,860
Jiang Anlan, I never expected
to see you in this position.

169
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:29,420
Don't worry, she'll say yes.

170
00:06:29,820 --> 00:06:31,180
Though I don't know

171
00:06:31,180 --> 00:06:32,980
what kind of proposal she likes,

172
00:06:32,980 --> 00:06:33,940
the key is

173
00:06:33,940 --> 00:06:35,220
who it's from.

174
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:38,380
Yuan just wants simple happiness.

175
00:06:39,830 --> 00:06:41,640
If she refuses, I'll drag her to the altar.

176
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:46,140
Boss, are you planning to bring your game
moves

177
00:06:46,420 --> 00:06:47,620
into real life?

178
00:07:07,140 --> 00:07:07,980
Yuan,

179
00:07:08,340 --> 00:07:10,140
Anlan's aunt came to see me today.

180
00:07:11,340 --> 00:07:12,620
She offered me money

181
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:14,780
to convince you to leave Anlan.

182
00:07:17,820 --> 00:07:18,900
But don't worry,

183
00:07:19,780 --> 00:07:21,420
I didn't take a single cent.

184
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:24,540
I may be useless,

185
00:07:25,060 --> 00:07:26,140
but I'd never your happiness

186
00:07:26,820 --> 00:07:27,860
for money.

187
00:07:32,580 --> 00:07:33,780
Thank you, Uncle.

188
00:07:37,620 --> 00:07:38,460
Yuan,

189
00:07:39,780 --> 00:07:41,260
did I ruin things for you?

190
00:07:42,820 --> 00:07:44,060
If I hadn't been careless

191
00:07:44,060 --> 00:07:45,380
and scalded Anlan's mother,

192
00:07:45,780 --> 00:07:47,220
maybe things wouldn't be like this.

193
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:50,940
No, Uncle.

194
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:52,220
Don't overthink it.

195
00:07:54,340 --> 00:07:55,220
Maybe it's because

196
00:07:55,220 --> 00:07:56,500
I was sick

197
00:07:57,180 --> 00:07:59,180
and didn't go to his father's birthday party.

198
00:08:02,700 --> 00:08:03,740
Or maybe,

199
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:07,180
none of those are the real reasons.

200
00:08:09,540 --> 00:08:10,380
Yuan,

201
00:08:10,860 --> 00:08:12,780
I knew you'd be upset hearing this.

202
00:08:13,900 --> 00:08:16,060
I truly want you to be happy.

203
00:08:17,300 --> 00:08:19,100
But if you aren't happy with him,

204
00:08:19,780 --> 00:08:21,300
I won't support this relationship.

205
00:08:31,460 --> 00:08:33,340
(Lord of All)

206
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:39,140
Hello.

207
00:08:40,340 --> 00:08:41,180
You knew?

208
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:43,820
Yeah.

209
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:46,380
Don't worry.

210
00:08:47,220 --> 00:08:48,260
I'll take care of it.

211
00:08:50,580 --> 00:08:51,940
Let's face it together.

212
00:08:54,270 --> 00:08:55,650
But I have to go on a business trip

213
00:08:56,180 --> 00:08:57,380
for a couple of days.

214
00:08:58,130 --> 00:08:59,250
See you when I get back.

215
00:09:02,140 --> 00:09:03,420
You're going on a business trip?

216
00:09:04,290 --> 00:09:05,220
Just two or three days.

217
00:09:06,580 --> 00:09:07,980
Call me if you miss me.

218
00:09:08,510 --> 00:09:09,610
I won't turn off my phone.

219
00:09:10,660 --> 00:09:11,740
And if you don't miss me,

220
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:13,220
you still have to call me.

221
00:09:13,780 --> 00:09:14,730
Because I'll miss you.

222
00:09:17,060 --> 00:09:18,660
Then why can't you call me?

223
00:09:20,380 --> 00:09:21,220
No reason.

224
00:09:21,860 --> 00:09:22,820
You must call me.

225
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:24,730
So you don't overthink it.

226
00:09:28,980 --> 00:09:29,820
Anlan,

227
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:33,500
we have to stay together, okay?

228
00:09:35,860 --> 00:09:36,700
Don't worry.

229
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:39,020
We won't be apart.

230
00:09:51,220 --> 00:09:52,620
Thanks for helping me out last time.

231
00:09:53,020 --> 00:09:54,940
I hate owing people favors.

232
00:09:55,260 --> 00:09:56,100
This meal's on me.

233
00:09:56,640 --> 00:09:58,500
You paid me back, so it's not a favor.

234
00:09:58,780 --> 00:09:59,620
It's on me.

235
00:10:00,380 --> 00:10:01,940
But that doesn't seem right.

236
00:10:01,940 --> 00:10:02,780
Don't argue with me.

237
00:10:02,980 --> 00:10:03,820
It's just a meal.

238
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:05,860
Besides, I picked the restaurant.

239
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,220
So I've got this.

240
00:10:09,580 --> 00:10:11,380
Ancheng, you're really a nice guy.

241
00:10:12,060 --> 00:10:13,180
Unlike some people

242
00:10:13,420 --> 00:10:14,660
who fake being rich

243
00:10:15,220 --> 00:10:16,380
but have no money

244
00:10:16,660 --> 00:10:17,620
in their pockets.

245
00:10:23,740 --> 00:10:24,580
Please enjoy.

246
00:10:24,580 --> 00:10:25,420
Thank you.

247
00:10:26,340 --> 00:10:27,490
This salmon here is good.

248
00:10:27,820 --> 00:10:28,660
Try some.

249
00:10:31,090 --> 00:10:31,930
Hmm.

250
00:10:42,940 --> 00:10:43,780
Delicious.

251
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:58,540
Ancheng,

252
00:10:59,100 --> 00:10:59,940
you're so thoughtful.

253
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:02,660
Your girlfriend must be very happy.

254
00:11:03,690 --> 00:11:04,660
I'm single.

255
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:07,020
No way.

256
00:11:07,460 --> 00:11:08,400
You're so outstanding.

257
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:10,460
Maybe your standards are too high.

258
00:11:11,780 --> 00:11:12,620
Aren't you the same?

259
00:11:15,140 --> 00:11:16,180
I guess

260
00:11:16,460 --> 00:11:17,940
I just haven't met the right one yet.

261
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:19,740
It would

262
00:11:19,740 --> 00:11:21,060
be so nice if I could find a guy

263
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:22,300
who takes good care of me,

264
00:11:22,300 --> 00:11:23,340
just like Anlan does

265
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:24,540
for Yao Yuan.

266
00:11:31,140 --> 00:11:32,060
He is quite caring.

267
00:11:35,380 --> 00:11:36,220
Are things

268
00:11:36,420 --> 00:11:37,420
going well for them?

269
00:11:38,300 --> 00:11:39,140
Pretty well.

270
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:40,820
They are always on the phone.

271
00:11:42,420 --> 00:11:43,620
Couples in love

272
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:46,460
are so enviable.

273
00:11:47,220 --> 00:11:49,180
I wonder when I can

274
00:11:49,660 --> 00:11:50,840
have a proper romance.

275
00:11:51,660 --> 00:11:52,990
Do you want to date that badly?

276
00:11:53,580 --> 00:11:54,420
Of course.

277
00:11:54,980 --> 00:11:56,220
At my age,

278
00:11:56,380 --> 00:11:58,060
I'm in my prime.

279
00:11:58,580 --> 00:12:00,660
If I don't date soon, I'll just wither away.

280
00:12:00,660 --> 00:12:01,740
What a waste of good years.

281
00:12:02,860 --> 00:12:04,980
So I won't let other people's opinions

282
00:12:04,980 --> 00:12:05,940
stop me.

283
00:12:06,220 --> 00:12:07,740
Youth only comes once.

284
00:12:08,780 --> 00:12:10,460
I just want to date.

285
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:12,540
Am I holding back the society

286
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:13,600
or something?

287
00:12:19,060 --> 00:12:19,900
Please enjoy.

288
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:22,940
Eat more.

289
00:12:22,940 --> 00:12:23,780
Mm.

290
00:12:32,660 --> 00:12:33,500
Want a ride home?

291
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:34,700
No, it's okay.

